	(293,1,'2017-02-16 12:51:25','2017-02-16 12:51:25','Co-operative Technologists (aka CoTech) is a network of co-operatives that sell tech/digital services. It aims to create a better technology sector in the UK that focuses primarily on worker, customer and end-user needs rather than on generating private profit.\r\n\r\nThe members of the network aim to use their collective experience, skills, resources and knowledge to radically increase the market share of companies that are owned and run by their workers. We have found that this model creates better workplaces, better digital products and better value for customers. We want to help more people to enjoy the benefits of this model.\r\n\r\nEach member of the network is a company that is owned and democratically run by it\'s workers (and, in some cases, customers). There are no private shareholders who take money out of the company and/or direct the company\'s activities. While many of the member co-operatives do not have completely flat structures - many have boards, management committees, etc. - they are all democratic workplaces and the members have the opportunity to appoint people to roles or change the structure of their organisations.\r\n\r\nGovernance of the network currently takes place through a rough consensus process using <a href=\"https://www.loomio.org/g/oVwtKDOn/digital-co-ops\">Loomio</a>, <a href=\"https://wiki.coops.tech/\">a wiki</a> and <a href=\"https://www.email-lists.org/mailman/listinfo/tech-coops\">a open email list</a>, and all members are invited and encouraged to get involved. As the network develops, we will explore changes to this governance model together.\r\n\r\nThe network was founded at <a href=\"https://wiki.coops.tech/wiki/Main_Page#Wortley_Hall_2016\">an event on 14th November 2016</a> at <a href=\"https://www.wortleyhall.org.uk/\">Wortley Hall - the worker\'s stately home</a> - where many of us met for the very first time to share ideas, skills and plans for world domination.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://wiki.coops.tech/w/images/a/ae/Pose.png\" alt=\"Co-operative Technologists at Wortley Hall\" width=\"1024\" height=\"376\" />\r\n\r\nRead <a href=\"/manifesto\">our manifesto</a>, <a href=\"/#contact\">contact us if you want to work with us</a> or <a href=\"/join\">join us</a>.','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','248-autosave-v1','','','2017-02-16 12:51:25','2017-02-16 12:51:25','',248,'http://mapping-cotech.test.outlandish.com/248-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(294,1,'2016-12-12 15:55:18','2016-12-12 15:55:18','<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>About Us</strong></p>\\r\\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">We are the Cooperative Technologists (or CoTech for short); a group of tech coops who have formed together to make one large collection of cooperatives, inspired byPrinciple 6, <i>Cooperation amongst</i> cooperatives, taken from the seven Cooperative Principles.</p>\\r\\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">On 14th November 2016, we allmet in Sheffield, at the Workers Stately Home, Worley Hall, some of us met for the very first time. We shared ideas, skills, needs and much, much more.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1024\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://wiki.coops.tech/w/images/a/ae/Pose.png\" width=\"1024\" height=\"376\" /> <span style=\"color: #999999;\">November 2016, Wortley Hall; the birth of CoTech</span>[/caption]\\r\\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Now, ware attempting something that has neverbeen attempted before. A network that can grow together. A network that can share resources, skills, work and time. A networkpassionate about creating a work environment that is fair to all workers. A network that is motivated by a world keen to create justice, not profit.</p>\\r\\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Read our manifesto and if you would like to work with us, or join the network, you can get in touch here.</p>','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','248-revision-v1','','','2016-12-12 15:55:18','2016-12-12 15:55:18','',248,'http://mapping-cotech.test.outlandish.com/248-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
