	(1652,1,'2017-02-14 13:04:11','2017-02-14 13:04:11','We believe in a fairer world in which wealth and resources are distributed to the people who need them rather than those best able to take them.\r\n\r\nAs <a href=\"https://dev.coops.tech/about/\">Co-operative Technologists</a> we aim to ensure the technology plays it\'s part in creating a fairer world.\r\n\r\nOur individual workers co-operatives have shown that workers who collectively own their companies and control their destinies make better workplaces, better suppliers and better digital products.\r\n\r\nWe call upon tech workers who share our vision to <a href=\"https://dev.coops.tech/join/\">join us</a>.\r\n\r\nWe call upon consumers of digital products - including trades unions, charities, governments and private companies - to reject the assumption the tech companies must be multinational conglomerates or private equity-funded startups. Technology is the lifeblood of our future not a gravy train.\r\n\r\nWe hereby give notice to technology companies that do not treat their employees fairly, do not give their workers control of their businesses and do not seek to create a fairer world that your days are numbered. We are more creative, more committed and more resilient. Join us.\r\n\r\nWorkers of the world, Swipe Left!','Manifesto','','inherit','closed','closed','','303-revision-v1','','','2017-02-14 13:04:11','2017-02-14 13:04:11','',303,'https://dev.coops.tech/303-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
